    <name>
      <text>Finding speeds of two people cycling toward each other from two towns</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>[[verbatim]]</strong></p>
<p>{@name1@} and {@name2@} start cycling toward each other from two towns {@distance_disp@} km apart. {@faster_name@} cycles {@speed_diff_disp@} km/h faster than {@slower_name@}. If they meet after {@time_disp@} hours:</p>
<p>Find their speeds.</p>
<p>{@faster_name@}'s speed: [[input:ans1]]  km/h [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>
<p>{@slower_name@}'s speed: [[input:ans2]] km/h [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>Let {@slower_name@}'s speed = \(v\) km/h.</p>
<p>Then {@faster_name@}'s speed = \(v + {@speed_diff_disp@}\) km/h.</p>

<p>When cycling toward each other, their relative speed is the sum:</p>
<p>\(v + (v + {@speed_diff_disp@}) = 2v + {@speed_diff_disp@}\) km/h</p>

<p>They cover {@distance_disp@} km in {@time_disp@} hour, so:</p>
<p>\((2v + {@speed_diff_disp@}) \times {@time_disp@} = {@distance_disp@}\)</p>
<p>\(2v + {@speed_diff_disp@} = \frac{ {@distance_disp@} }{ {@time_disp@} }\)</p>
<p>\(2v = {@distance_disp/time_disp@} - {@speed_diff_disp@}\)</p>
<p>\(v = \frac{ {@distance_disp/time_disp@} - {@speed_diff_disp@} }{2} = {@answer2@} \text{ km/h}\)</p>

<p>{@faster_name@}'s speed = \(v + {@speed_diff_disp@} = {@answer2@} + {@speed_diff_disp@} = {@answer1@} \text{ km/h}\)</p>

<p>Therefore, their speeds are:</p>
<ul>
  <li>{@faster_name@}: {@ta1@} km/h</li>
  <li>{@slower_name@}: {@ta2@} km/h</li>
</ul>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
